      "writtenOn": "2020-04-19T00:20:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m a bit concerned that if we trigger based on this condition, we end up re-applying for all descendants and create local pctx copies unnecessarily.  E.g.:\n\n  \u003cg id\u003d\"g1\" fill\u003d\"currentColor\"\u003e\n    \u003cg id\u003d\"g2\" color\u003d\"blue\"\u003e\n      \u003cg id\u003d\"g3\"\u003e\n         \u003cg id\u003d\"g4\u003e\n           ...\n         \u003c/g\u003e\n      \u003c/g\u003e\n    \u003c/g\u003e\n  \u003c/g\u003e\n\nWe seem to trigger for everything below/including g1, when in reality nothing changes below g2.  I wonder if it would be sufficient to force an update only when we have a local color (g2 above)?  See next comment.",
      "revId": "da33e99868d425eed0d5be0d018798a10169bf00",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
